parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Pressure Issues (Sumping) in Milwaukee 8 Engine
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pressure system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries due to oil blowing back under the rear tires, and potentially lead to engine seizure.
symptoms: Sudden loss of oil pressure
excessive smoke from the exhaust and breather tubes
oil blowing back under the rear tires
low oil level
crankcase pressure
and oil cap blowing out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pressure switch can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Oil pressure switch working its way out
low oil pressure indication
and oil pouring out when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially in stop-and-go traffic or when pulling into a parking lot.
symptoms: Engine stalling during stop-and-go traffic or when pulling into a parking lot
excessive vibration
and jerking of the motorcycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive vibration and heating can cause discomfort, minor burns, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Excessive vibration
jerking
and heating of the motorcycle
causing discomfort and minor burns.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect for Recall Remedies
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for recall remedies can lead to prolonged exposure to potential safety risks, causing inconvenience and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive notification of recall
but dealerships are unable to perform the recall repair due to unavailability of parts
leading to extended wait times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch to disengage can cause loss of control, accidents, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of the brake rotors can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Scraping noise coming from the rear brake
worn brake pads and rotors at low mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Leading to Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brakes can cause the motorcycle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Motorcycle pulls to one side when brakes are applied
failure to stop
front end snaps
loss of control.
